{{see|negro}}

==English==

===Proper noun===
'''Negro''' plural negros, negroes (Often capitalized) 
#''Archaic.'' A person of [[sub-Saharan]] [[African]] descent; [[black]].
#: The mental inferiority of the ''negro'' to the white or yellow races is a fact.--F. Manetta<p>In certain of the characteristics . . . the ''negro'' would appear to stand on a lower evolutionary plane than the white man, and to be more closely related to the highest anthropoids. The characteristics are length of arm, prognathism, a heavy massive cranium with large zygomatic arches, flat nose depressed at base, &c.--''Encyclopaedia Britannica,'' "negro," 11th ed., p. 344

